Fall picture day will be Wednesday, Sept. 9th. All students must have their picture taken for the yearbook, regardless of whether or not you plan to purchase pictures. The elementary and jr.high/high school have different ID's.

post_text: This is a reminder that ALL 7th grade students need 1 dose of the Tdap and 1 dose of the meningococcal vaccine before entering 7th grade in the fall. Senior students must receive a dose of Meningococcal Conjugate Vaccine before entering 12th grade in the fall. Please provide a copy of the updated immunization record for the school nurse. If you have further questions, please contact our nurse Kristen Ewers.

post_text:
Our elementary principal, Mr. Morr, has an important message for elementary parents of students in preschool through first grade:

We are having a parent informational meeting for preschool, kindergarten and first grade families. I, along with the teachers, will be sharing a number of school related topics with you prior to our first day of school on Monday, August 24. The meeting will be held in the varsity gymnasium on Tuesday, August 18.

The preschool meeting will start at 5:00. The kindergarten meeting will start at 6:00 and our 1st grade meeting will start at 7:00. Students are not required to attend and unfortunately, we will not be visiting the classrooms on this night.

Thanks, and we look forward to seeing you on Tuesday evening, August 18.

post_text:
Parents, this is just a reminder that all students will be wearing masks when school starts.

If you are considering homeschooling your son/daughter, this has to be done with the Northwest Ohio Educational Service Center. You will need to contact them for the enrollment procedure. Students will be permitted to participate in extracurriculars, band and choir if wanted.

If you are considering our online school, NOVA, you will need to contact either the elementary office or high school office by Monday, Aug. 17. A meeting with the school counselor and
the NOVA teacher will be set up to get the student enrolled. Students will be permitted to participate in extracurriculars, band and choir if wanted.

Any other online option would mean that the student is not a North Central student and would not be permitted to participate in our extracurriculars.

post_text: There has been a key update to the NC Restart Plan for this unprecedented start to a new school year. NC is happy to announce that our remote learning option now includes grades K-12. Please contact either the high school or elementary offices before August 17, 2020, to let them know if you would like your child to be a part of the NC Remote Learning Program of NOVA for the 1st semester of this school year. NC also plans to follow the new order of Gov. DeWine which states that students in school will need to wear a face covering. More detailed info about our NC Restart Plan can be found on our web site.

post_text: This is a message from Coach Mallett regarding JH volleyball. Any girl interested in JH volleyball, please check your school email. We will be starting practice Monday, August 3 at 3:00 in the JH gym. Please come prepared, dressed and ready to go as well as bringing your own water or drink. You must have your sports physical to be able to practice but if you do not have that completed, please attend practice anyway so that we can get an idea of how many girls would like to play. So far we only have three 7th graders and six 8th graders. So, come out and encourage your friends to join us to have some fun and learn the game of volleyball.

This is an important update from Dr. Rozevink for our new graduates. The consensus of the students who responded to her inquiry about a second commencement was that they would not attend, so there will NOT be another commencement on July 19. Most of you indicated that you did not think a second one would be necessary or that you did not plan to attend.

However, a few students responded with a suggestion about having the traditional brunch/lunch. Dr. Rozevink talked with Mr. Taylor and we are now planning a "parking lot food truck lunch" for all of you who can attend! It will be from 1:00-2:30 p.m. on July 19. This will give you another chance to get together with your classmates so spread the word to those who do not read their email! Bring your own chairs. We will have food. Of course, we will have to maintain social distancing, but we can still enjoy each other's company!

post_text: Please come out and show your support to the North Central Class of 2020! Their graduation celebration will be held tomorrow, Sunday, May 31 and transmitted in the parking lot on radio channel 1700 AM at 2:00 p.m. At approximately 3:00 p.m. at the conclusion of the ceremony, the Graduating Class of 2020 will participate in their final "Drive Through" in Pioneer. To view this special graduation event while being careful to observe social distancing, we invite the community to line the sidewalks starting at the front of the school and then extending from Baubice Street to Cedar Street. From there, the vehicles will travel onto Industrial Street and then to State Street. The event will end at Mill Street. (This is the same parade route as that taken for the Pioneer Days Parade which travels along Main Street.) We invite you to come out and support our seniors on their final appearance. Signs are more than welcome!

Hello, NC Families!
The staff at NC is missing your smiling faces! Even though the year didn't end how we planned, we still want to keep the tradition of waving another school year goodbye and wishing you all a wonderful summer! Our plan for this is to have the teachers line up along Baubice Street, in front of the school, between 3:00-3:15 p.m. on what would have been the last day of school (May 29). Please feel free to drive by during this time period to wave at the staff. We would ask that you still respect social distancing in order to keep everybody safe. We are looking forward to seeing you all!

post_text:
Parents of elementary students may pick up their child's personal belongings on either Tuesday, May 12 or Tuesday, May 19 from 12:30 to 4:30 p.m..

Please come to the elementary building and you will be assisted by a staff member while you wait in your car. Your child's personal items will be brought to your vehicle.

You may return educational packets at this time including any remaining PE, art, or music assignments. It is time to complete all outstanding student assignments for teacher review. Other items such as school text books may be returned at this time as well.

For grades 2-11, all library books and all laptops, laptop bags and their power cables will be collected on May 27-29 to allow time to finish all assignments. More specific details will be forthcoming. Please do not turn in computers before the collection dates of May 27-29. Also, all HS and JH textbooks will be collected on these days.

Thank you for your cooperation and we miss our Eagle students!

post_text:
Dear NC School Community,

This afternoon Governor Mike DeWine announced all schools in Ohio would remain closed for the rest of this school year (2019-2020). Our remote/online education and "packets" must continue for the rest of this school year. Because of this announcement, we will need to do additional planning to be sure how this will all come together for the remainder of this year. Thank you so much for your continued support of North Central Schools! We are truly NC STRONG!

Sincerely,
William D. Hanak
Superintendent

post_text: Harvest Market will be doing a food giveaway this Wednesday at the Enrichment Center from 10:00 a.m.-1:00 p.m. They are bringing the National Guard to distribute boxes of food to the first 100 households. No one will be allowed out of their vehicles. You will be registered at your car window and then will need to pop their trunk/hatch and one of the National Guard members will put a box of food in the vehicle. Please make sure your trunk/hatch area has room as the National Guard will not rearrange items in your vehicle. The building will not be open (no bathrooms).

post_text:
Governor DeWine has extended school-building closures until May 1 in the state of Ohio. As a result, our kindergarten screening scheduled for April 8 & 9 will be postponed. A future screening will be rescheduled for a date and time yet to be determined. We apologize for this inconvenience, and we will keep your child's kindergarten registration information on file.

Thank you!
Andy Morr
Elementary Principal

post_text: We were in our classrooms today working hard on preparing learning packets for our first graders! It just wasn’t the same walking into the empty classrooms knowing we wouldn’t see our little friends' smiling faces. We sure miss our first graders! So here’s a picture of our smiling faces! We wish for everyone to stay healthy and safe! We love you all!

PBS Stations: Public TV New Programming for Students and Teachers
1. Ohio’s PBS stations have developed a new on-air schedule of at-home programming for students and teachers. This will make resources available to homes that have limited internet access.
2. The Ohio “At Home Learning” initiative includes a full schedule of daily television programming geared toward students in prekindergarten through 12th grade.
3. This programming will be available on Ohio PBS television stations across the state starting in most areas on Monday, March 30, 2020.
4. More information about this programming www.pbslearningmedia.org.
Broadcast TV Channels: 22, 27.1, 27.2, 27.3
Spectrum Channels: 2, 3, 994
Dish & Direct TV Channel: 27

post_text: We will begin our breakfast/ lunch distribution program on Monday, March 23, 2020. Monday each student will receive 3 breakfast and lunch meals. Thursday each student will receive 2 breakfast and lunch meals. We will have a drive-thru line for all students in Pioneer to pick up meals. The line will be in north parking lot by the auditeria, off Baubice Street from 11:00 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Pick up person must have the student first and last name with student ID number. Please order in advance. Students on a regular bus stop can get meals delivered to a regular bus stop. All orders for delivery need to be requested by 7:00 a.m. of the delivery day, as we will start deliveries around 10:00 a.m. Deliveries must be ordered in advance by contacting Rob Taylor (rtaylor@northcentralschool.org) at NCLS.

Please continue promoting everyday disease prevention strategies:
-If you are sick, stay home.
-Avoid close contact with those who are already sick.
-Cover your nose and mouth when coughing or sneezing with a tissue or the crook of your arm.
-Wash your hands often with soap and water.
-Avoid touching eyes, nose, or mouth.

For those students taking the Hunter’s Education Course, the state of Ohio would like you to pre-register for the class. To do so, follow the steps listed below. This will save a lot of time after you have finished the class.
-This link ( https://oh-web.s3licensing.com/Event/Index ) takes you to the registration page.
-Enter the event passcode of 1000047828.
-Click on "New Customer" button.
-Fill out all the fields.
-Check the box "I hereby declare all information provided is true and correct."
-Click continue.
-Follow another on screen directions.

If questions or concerns, please email the following:
NShamp@NorthCentralSchool.org

post_text: The indoor track team finished their season this past weekend at the 2020 Midwest Indoor Championship. Alexia Miller placed 9th in the 60m dash with a new school record of 8.74. Jack Bailey set a new indoor long jump record! In the 200m dash, Alexia Miller placed 13th, Sarah Laney 15th, and Ashlyn Helms 18th. The 4x200 girls relay team of Faler, Miller, Helms, and Laney placed 4th with a new school record! In pole vault, Kassidy Faler placed 18th and Ashlyn Helms placed 20th. Zachary Tomblin finished 13th in the 1600m run. Evan Livengood finished 9th in the 60m hurdles. The boys 4x200m relay of Cruz, Bailey, Hayes, and Tomblin finished in 10th place. Zack Hayes medaled and placed 3rd in high jump. In the boys shot put, Kaiden Russell placed 11th, Coltan Willson placed 14th, and Drake Schorling placed 15th. Great season!

Zachary Tomblin finished 13th in the 1600m run. Evan Livengood finished 9th in the 60m hurdles. The boys 4x200m relay of Cruz, Bailey, Hayes, and Tomblin finished in 10th place. Zack Hayes medaled and placed 3rd in high jump. In the boys shot put, Kaiden Russell placed 11th, Coltan Willson placed 14th, and Drake Schorling placed 15th. Great season!

post_text: On May 14 there will be a Hunter’s Education class held in the Eagle Room at North Central High School. It will begin at 7:50 and end at 2:50. This will be available to any student 11 years old and up. Students will be excused from class, but will be responsible for any work missed. It is also open to any community member that wants to get their Hunters Education card. This is a free class offered through the OARS program at NC. The department of Wildlife and the Sportsmen’s Alliance will be teaching the class. All wishing to attend need to sign up on Mr. Shamp’s door or email Mr. Shamp at nshamp@northcentralschool.org so we get an accurate count of attendees. Attendees can bring a sack lunch or purchase a lunch in the school cafeteria. Seating will be limited, so this will be first come, first served. All attendees will need to have their last 4 digits of their social security number with them when they fill out the required document for the state to process the information at the end of the class.
